Test cases for 'buckle and'.

This should be a danceable sequence.

sdr> /program = C4
C4
sdr> sides split swap ; veer left ; centers hinge
|      2B>
| 
| 2G^  3G<  3Bv
| 
| 1B^  1G>  4Gv
| 
|      4B<
sdr> buckle and do 2/3 of a recycle
| 1Bv  2Gv
| 
| 4B^  3Gv
| 
| 1G^  2Bv
| 
| 4G^  3B^
sdr> cheerio
| 3Gv  1Bv  2Gv  4Bv
| 
| 2B^  4G^  3B^  1G^
sdr> buckle and dixie diamond
| 2Bv  1Gv
| 
|   3B>
| 
| 4G^  2Gv
| 
|   1B<
| 
| 3G^  4B^
sdr> ends divide
      3B>
 2BV       1GV
    4G^ 2GV
 3G^       4B^
      1B<
sdr> /// "lines diamond circulate thru"
sdr> centers diamond circulate while the ends circulate
sdr> buckle and flip the diamond
sdr> reverse the diamond
sdr> clear the centers for a shakedown
sdr> centers pass thru
sdr> side boys face left
sdr> short and sweet
sdr> /// circulate, grand working forward walk and dodge,
sdr> /// head boys 1/2, all u-turn back... or just
sdr> reverse single file promenade home
sdr> /exit
